# Planet Crafter Mod Context

Use this when working on LogisticsInfo or related modding questions.

## Where to Find References

- **Game**: `C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Planet Crafter`
- **Managed DLLs**: `Planet Crafter_Data\Managed\` (Assembly-CSharp, UnityEngine, etc.)
- **BepInEx**: `BepInEx\core\` (BepInEx.dll, 0Harmony.dll)
- **Decompiled code**: `C:\Work\Modding\PlanetCrafter-Modding\decompiled\Assembly-CSharp\` (source files, especially `SpaceCraft\`)

## How to Get Information

1. **Game classes/methods** – Inspect decompiled `SpaceCraft\*.cs` (e.g. `MachineAutoCrafter`, `UiWindowGroupSelector`, `LogisticManager`, `InventoryAssociated`).
2. **Method signatures for Harmony** – Use exact signatures from decompiled code before patching.
3. **Example mods** – `C:\Work\Modding\PlanetCrafter-Modding\ThePlanetCrafterMods` or `https://github.com/akarnokd/ThePlanetCrafterMods`
4. **Skills** – When creating/updating Planet Crafter mods, use the **planet-crafter-bepinex-mod** skill (DLL paths, csproj template, patch patterns, build/deploy).

## Build & Deploy

**Manual:**
```powershell
dotnet build -c Release
Copy-Item ".\bin\Release\netstandard2.1\LogisticsInfo.dll" "C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Planet Crafter\BepInEx\plugins\LogisticsInfo.dll" -Force
```

**Scripts:**
- `.\deploy.ps1` — Build and copy DLL to game's BepInEx/plugins. Or double-click `deploy.bat`.
- `.\pack.ps1` — Build and create Nexus distribution zip (`dist\LogisticsInfo-{version}.zip`).

**Nexus Mods:**
- Zip contains only the DLL at root (Vortex installs to BepInEx/plugins automatically).
- Version is read from `PluginVersion` in Plugin.cs.
- Close the game before deploy if the DLL is locked.
